			</classificationInformation>
			<CASNumber>CID 11430</CASNumber>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Potassium carbonate, K2CO3, appears as a white powder or as colorless solid crystal and has a salty taste. It may be used in pharmaceutical laboratories as a drying agent or as a source of potassium. It also used in fire extinguishers, to make soap, to make glass, and to soften water. It is a white salt that forms a strongly alkaline solution and is used in making glass and soap. It is a white powder that is water-soluble but insoluble in ethanol. Potassium carbonate reacts well with water to ultimately form an alkaline solution.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">碳酸钾（K2CO3）呈白色粉末或无色固体晶体，有咸味。它可用作制药实验室的干燥剂或钾源。它还可用于灭火器、制造肥皂、制造玻璃和软化水。它是一种白色盐，可形成强碱性溶液，用于制造玻璃和肥皂。它是一种白色粉末，可溶于水，但不溶于乙醇。碳酸钾与水反应良好，最终形成碱性溶液。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>K2CO3</sumFormula>
